// Design system documentation in CSS
/*
Design System Documentation
==========================

Colors
------
- Primary: Used for primary actions and key elements
- Secondary: Used for secondary actions and supporting elements
- Background: Used for page and surface backgrounds
- Text: Used for text content with different emphasis levels
- Status: Used for indicating success, warning, error, and info states

Typography
----------
- Display: Used for headings and large text
- Body: Used for paragraph text and general content
- Mono: Used for code and monospaced text

Spacing
-------
- xxs (4px): Micro spacing for tight elements
- xs (8px): Small spacing for padding and margins
- sm (12px): Medium spacing for components
- md (16px): Default spacing for components
- lg (24px): Large spacing for sections
- xl (32px): Extra large spacing for layouts
- xxl (48px): Huge spacing for major sections
- xxxl (64px): Massive spacing for page layouts

Components
----------
- Card: Container for content with header, body, and footer
- Alert: Feedback messages with status colors
- Badge: Small labels for status or categories
*/

